2.21	The_Entombment_(Pontormo)	The Deposition from the Cross (Pontormo)	The Deposition from the Cross is an altarpiece of the Deposition of Christ by the Italian Renaissance painter Jacopo Pontormo, completed in 1528. It is broadly considered to be the artist's surviving masterpiece. Painted in oil on wood, The Deposition is located above the altar of the Capponi Chapel at the church of Santa Felicita, in Florence.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Jacopo_Pontormo_-_Kreuzabnahme_Christi.jpg/300px-Jacopo_Pontormo_-_Kreuzabnahme_Christi.jpg
